description:
Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents the return of the Green Hornet! In 2010, Dynamite will unveil three brand-new Green Hornet series, starting with the worldwide debut of Kevin Smith's vision for the masked crusader (based on his unproduced screenplay)! Get a first look with this special edition featuring not only Smith's version, but the award-winning work of creators Matt Wagner and Brett Matthews as well! All in one Free Comic Book Day comic event!

Includes the previews of:

Green Hornet #1

Green Hornet: Year One #1

The Green Hornet Strikes! #1

Kato Origins #1

Kato #1
name: Free Comic Book Day Edition

volume.name: Green Hornet #1 Free Comic Book Day Edition

description: Building on the success of First Born and Broken Trinity, Top Cow finally reveals the secrets of all 13 Artifacts - which include The Darkness, Witchblade, Angelus, Magdalena's Spear of Destiny, and more. Launching a massive 13-issue event beginning in July 2010, this series will literally define and redefine the nature of the Top Cow Universe! The final identity of the remaining hidden Artifacts will be revealed, characters will perish, and the very existence of the Top Cow Universe will be at stake. And it begins here!

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: In "Twas The Crime Before Christmas," a pregnant woman and her husband are wandering the streets of a major city, sought by two groups of people. It sounds like O. Henry's story "Gift of the Magi" all over again but the city is modern-day New York; the mother and father are mob informants; ant the wise men and shepherds are mob gunman, Jennifer, and Gabe!
name: Twas the Crime Before Christmas...

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that chalenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
Gabe and Jennifer plan to spend a lovely, quiet weekend at Gabe's place, getting caught up on some personal time. But their professional services are needed when the tenants' rent strike turns violent. Gabe's downstairs neighbor is murdered - and Gabe is framed for the crime!

This is the first issue published by Innovation. It picks up directly where the Comico series left off with the numbering sequence.
name: A New Lease on Death

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
In "The English Channeler Mystery," witness Gabe, Jennifer, and famous sleuth Ellery Queen stalk a killer who moves through sand without a clue - and who has been dead for 10,000 years! Margaret Chalmers-Rune claims that she can channel the spirit of Noraga, whose body "died 10 centuries ago when the seas swallowed Atlantis," but Margaret is poisoned after delivering an ominous message... and her husband asks Ellery Queen to solve the case. Meanwhile, her stepson and daughter have engaged Jennifer and Gabe. As the bodies pile up, Gabe and Ellery both try to deduce the identity of the killer. Who will solve the crime first.

This issue was written by Mike W. Barr with the full permission of Ellery Queen magazine celibrating the 60th anniversary of the super sleuth.
name: The English Channeler Mystery

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: In "Deadly Anniversary," Gabe Webb meets the parents of his sweetie Jennifer! And if things weren't tense enough, one of the house guests is trying to murder Jennifer's father on the eve of his 40th wedding anniversary. This issue also reveals more of Jennifer's past -- to both Gabe's delight and consternation!
name: Deadly Anniversary

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: In "Murderer's Mask," a porcelain death mask of a beautiful woman, long dead, leads to attempted murder -- and to the cavernous mansion of a reclusive billionaire. It's sex, murder, money, and mystery in an extra-long story lovingly illustrated by Adam Hughes for this special issue!
name: Murderer's Mask

description:
Overview

A preview to the upcoming War of the Supermen. In the events following Braniac's attack of New Krypton, Superman confronts General Zod about his plans to send the Kryptonian armed forces to Earth. Can he stop Zod before he makes a mistake that may destroy two worlds?

In a second feature, Lois Lane summarizes the events of the past two years that have led to Zod's order.
name: War of the Supermen, Prologue; Filling In The Blanks

description: This sampler is the perfect place to check out the sensational line of titles aimed at readers of all ages! It includes exciting, all-new stories starring Batman: The Brave & The Bold, Tiny Titans, Billy Batson & the Magic of Shazam! and Super Friends!
name: Mega Sampler 2010

description: Last year's comic book industry event is this year's best way to get more readers hooked on Mark Waid's best-selling original title, Irredeemable, the series that dared to ask the question: what if the world's greatest hero decided to become the world's greatest villain? And 12 issues later, that question has been answered with a best-selling comic series, two best-selling trade collections and Incorruptible, the companion series.

volume.name: Irredeemable / Incorruptible Free Comic Book Day Edition

description: Usagi is given a mysterious ceramic persimmon by a dying man, and the ronin promises to deliver the artifact to the man's lord. But the simple promise becomes more complicated when Usagi's life is threatened over the bauble! He must run a gauntlet of assassins and unravel the secret of the green persimmon in time to stop a civil war!
name: Green Persimmon

description: The plans of Cobra, Chuckles, and the agents following him all collide. Can anyone survive? Will the Joes get what they want from Chuckles... by any means necessary? And brace yourself for a last page that will impact the entire line of G.I. Joe books!
name: Cold-Blooded

description: The wedding and the honeymoon are over for comicdom's favorite super couple, so what's next? Getting settled, starting their new life… and finding out what really happened at the reception. It's a whole new start for "Love and Capes", and a great lead-in to the second trade coming from IDW in summer 2010!

name: Hell`s Hottest Acre
